			<ns0:name>pa...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101628056640429344673/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I assume the partial validation mode should accept an instruction in presence of trailing bytes, should return the validation status, length of the instruction. Anything else?

Technically lack of partial-validation mode does not prevent comprehensive testing because we can use the ragel-based enumerator to prove that the R-DFA accepts a subset of what the orig validator accepted. The ragel-based enumerator currently only enumerates all recognizable instructions, but it could be made to enumerate only instructions that can be found in a valid nacl stream.

However, the partial-validation mode should be relatively easy to implement, and we want to do that for more uniform testing.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-06-13T18:43:26.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-06-13T18:43:26.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
